<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <%- include('./partials/header') %>
        <title>
            <%= title %>
        </title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/docs.css">
</head>

<body>
    <%- include('./partials/nav', { searchQuery: '' }) %>

        <div class="docs-wrapper">
            <!-- Left Sidebar (Navigation) -->
            <aside class="docs-sidebar-left">
                <div class="docs-nav-group">
                    <div class="docs-nav-title">Company</div>
                    <a href="/about" class="docs-nav-link">About Lumina</a>
                    <a href="/mission" class="docs-nav-link">Our Mission</a>
                </div>
                <div class="docs-nav-group">
                    <div class="docs-nav-title">Legal</div>
                    <a href="/privacy" class="docs-nav-link">Privacy Policy</a>
                    <a href="/terms" class="docs-nav-link active">Terms of Service</a>
                </div>
                <div class="docs-nav-group">
                    <div class="docs-nav-title">Support</div>
                    <a href="mailto:support@lumina.com" class="docs-nav-link">Contact Us</a>
                </div>
            </aside>

            <!-- Main Content -->
            <main class="docs-main">
                <div class="docs-header">
                    <h1 class="docs-title">Terms of Service</h1>
                    <div class="docs-meta">Effective Date: <%= new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric'
                            , month: 'long' , day: 'numeric' }) %>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="docs-content">
                    <p>
                        Welcome to Lumina. By using our platform, you're agreeing to these terms. It's mutual trust with
                        a little bit of legalese.
                    </p>

                    <h2 id="acceptance">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
                    <p>
                        By creating an account, you agree to abide by these terms. We want to build a safe, respectful
                        community, and these rules help us do that.
                    </p>

                    <h2 id="conduct">2. User Conduct</h2>
                    <p>Lumina is a place for ideas, not hate. You agree NOT to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Post illegal, harmful, threatening, or harassing content.</li>
                        <li>Spam other users or use automated bots.</li>
                        <li>Attempt to hack, reverse engineer, or disrupt our services.</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2 id="ownership">3. Content Ownership</h2>
                    <p>
                        <strong>You own your words.</strong> When you post on Lumina, you retain full ownership of your
                        content. You grant us a license to display it to the world, but the IP remains yours.
                    </p>

                    <h2 id="termination">4. Termination</h2>
                    <p>
                        We reserve the right to suspend accounts that violate these terms. We will always try to provide
                        a warning, but zero-tolerance violations (like hate speech) may result in immediate bans.
                    </p>

                    <h2 id="disclaimer">5. Disclaimer</h2>
                    <p>
                        Lumina is provided "as is". We strive for 99.9% uptime and perfection, but software is software.
                        We aren't liable for any digital hiccups.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </main>

            <!-- Right Sidebar (Table of Contents) -->
            <aside class="docs-sidebar-right">
                <div class="toc-title">On this page</div>
                <nav class="toc-nav">
                    <a href="#acceptance" class="toc-link">Acceptance</a>
                    <a href="#conduct" class="toc-link">User Conduct</a>
                    <a href="#ownership" class="toc-link">Content Ownership</a>
                    <a href="#termination" class="toc-link">Termination</a>
                    <a href="#disclaimer" class="toc-link">Disclaimer</a>
                </nav>
            </aside>
        </div>

        <%- include('./partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>